00:42.540 --> 00:50.420
This is Bill Vernon and Daryl Lane. Jo Clayton is a science fiction and fantasy
writer who is a discovery of Donald A. Wollheim, publisher of DAW Books. Other

00:50.420 --> 00:58.200
recent Wollheim discoveries are C.J. Cherryh and Tanith Lee. Clayton has published
seven novels in the Diadem series and two in the Duel of Sorcery series. She has

00:58.200 --> 01:05.720
also published several short stories. Clayton began writing only after she was
well into her career. We asked her why she decided to become a writer and why

01:05.720 --> 01:20.160
she chose science fiction. I've been teaching for a number of years. And I'm
also an artist. I draw a lot. And I was much more interested in painting and

01:20.160 --> 01:35.440
drawing for my first years than I was in writing. But I gradually came to see
that while I have a gift for rendering, I can do quite good individual objects.

01:35.440 --> 01:49.680
I don't have any feel for design. And I wasn't willing to take the trouble to
get work for that deal. So I decided to remain very much an amateur as a

01:49.680 --> 02:07.020
painter. But having drawn that conclusion and being in a situation where I
needed to get out, I was about ready to bang my head against the walls. I'm not

02:07.020 --> 02:21.160
going to be your examples of teacher burnout. And so I started writing as a way
of breaking away from the job I was in. And science fiction, well, because I've

02:21.160 --> 02:33.120
always loved it, because I thought I could write it. And it is an awful lot of
fun making up worlds. Basically, that's it. Clayton's first novel, published in

02:33.120 --> 02:41.100
1977, was Diadem from the Stars. She's published six more novels in the series
since then. The protagonist is Aleytys, a strange girl from a backward planet

02:41.100 --> 02:49.060
who accidentally acquires the Diadem, an alien artifact which contains the
essences and identities of three remarkable humans. We asked Clayton if she had

02:49.060 --> 02:56.680
the entire series planned before she wrote the first novel. It's like just about
every one of the novels that I write. I know where I'm starting, and I know my

02:56.680 --> 03:06.900
characters, and I know my world. In this case, it's a series of worlds. And I
know where I'm going, but how I'm going to get there develops. I don't think I

03:06.900 --> 03:16.740
could write any other way. I mean, it would be boring if I knew everything
before I started. For example, in Star Hunters, one of the secondary leads in

03:16.740 --> 03:30.140
that, the woman who was more or less a toy, a plaything, the wife of one of the
other secondary leads in the subplot, is only supposed to be in there for about

03:30.140 --> 03:39.720
three pages and so. But I suddenly got very interested in her, or she got me
interested in her, and she began to take over, and she became a very important

03:39.720 --> 03:47.680
part of the book. And this was totally, totally unexpected. During each
installment in the Diadem series, Aleytys learns more about her past and her

03:47.680 --> 03:58.460
quest. Here Clayton tells us of her plans for Aleytys in the series. In the
beginning, I meant to have Aleytys reach her, find her mother and her family in,

03:58.460 --> 04:09.240
well, about the same as the number of books. I think there'll be about nine in
all. I just finished one and turned it in. I think that's the eighth. And the

04:09.240 --> 04:14.980
next one will probably be the last in that particular series, dealing with
Aleytys as the main character.

04:17.920 --> 04:31.820
Each book, I hope, shows, makes Aleytys a little bit more aware of who she is
and what she really wants rather than what she thought she wanted. And in the

04:31.820 --> 04:44.200
end, she's going to end up, I hope, satisfied with where she is working and
living in that place for a while anyway. So I knew I was going to have her find

04:44.200 --> 04:54.480
her mother and her mother's world. How I was going to get there, depending upon
the inspiration and the desperation of the moment. We'll have more on our next

04:54.480 --> 04:55.460
show with Jo Clayton.

