23:50.360 --> 23:54.480
Coming up next is the Science Fiction Radio Show, so stay with us.

24:10.560 --> 24:15.920
This is the Science Fiction Radio Show, a commentary on science fiction and
fantasy.

24:18.880 --> 24:20.460
And here are your hosts.

24:24.900 --> 24:33.580
This is Bill Vernon. And Daryl Lane. Ann Maxwell began a new science fiction
series with the publication of Fire Dancer in 1982. Dancer's Luck and Dancer's

24:33.580 --> 24:40.460
Illusion have come out since then. Unlike Maxwell's other science fiction
series, this one consists of tightly connected novels. Maxwell's writing

24:40.460 --> 24:49.260
philosophy in the Fire Dancer series is quite different from that she used to
write the Concord series. I'm sure you've noticed the break between, say, Jaws

24:49.260 --> 25:00.460
of Menx and Fire Dancer. It's the break not only of the universe that it was
written in, but of the intent of the books themselves. Fire Dancer. I sat down

25:00.460 --> 25:08.720
intending to write a full-on, very accessible romp and enjoyed it thoroughly.
And from the response from the readers, I can only say they must have too.

25:10.600 --> 25:24.000
Whereas with the earlier books, the Concord books, they are less accessible, far
more multilayered, and certainly did not attract the larger audience that the

25:24.000 --> 25:33.200
Fire Dancer series has. They're just different books. The Fire Dancer series is
built around the relationship between Rheba, a Senyan dancer, and her Bre'n

25:33.200 --> 25:41.140
mentor, Kirtn. Rheba is a young dancer who literally commands energy. When she
dances, the energy streams from her as if it were fire. Kirtn, who is of an

25:41.140 --> 25:48.640
alien species, helps Rheba learn to control and modulate her powers. Rheba and
Kirtn are among the last of their respective races, and they are attempting in

25:48.640 --> 25:55.800
the series to locate other survivors. Since it's not spelled out in the series,
we asked Maxwell to tell us how the relationship between the dancers and the

25:55.800 --> 26:06.620
Bre'n might have evolved. They are constructs, as all is a construct, in that
sense. In other words, we are talking about a universe in which the, what we

26:06.620 --> 26:19.120
would call human, or whatever you want to call it, is not new. It has evolved
independently. It has evolved with self-force evolution. It has evolved in other

26:19.120 --> 26:31.600
people's labs against their will. This is a, not a world in which logic, as we
understand it, biology, is always going to be followed through. It is simply a

26:31.600 --> 26:44.840
universe in which that which could survive and was created, did, and has. And
when you come to the darkness between the cycles, then you get a, both

26:44.840 --> 26:58.620
a flowering and a weeding out. And what can survive that darkness does in a
changed form. In this sense, what we are talking about is the potential for a

26:58.620 --> 27:15.780
deep telepathy that became realized to the point that it was necessary. It was a
necessary channel for the Bre'n and for the dancers who lack, whose gifts come

27:15.780 --> 27:27.720
upon them rather all at once, and lack the ability to control them at first.
Then you, you become a situation where you are a symbiont, but not in the normal

27:27.720 --> 27:39.700
physical sense. They can live separately. You can feed them separately.
Generally, they will lose themselves. They, to be, to reach anything approaching

27:39.700 --> 27:53.040
their fullest potential, they must be paired. However, not all Bre'ns and not
all Senyasi are dancers, and the ones who aren't, are the basic changes that

27:53.040 --> 28:01.160
they need to rest at all. There are many unanswered questions remaining after
three installments of the Fire Dancer series. We asked Maxwell if she plans to

28:01.160 --> 28:12.320
wrap it up soon. Well, I must say that I would never, in one sense, totally
resolve the dancer thing. In other words, even if they do achieve some of Rheba's

28:12.460 --> 28:27.580
goals, that is a beginning as well as an ending. If you have a whole new planet
of dancers plus the residue of slaves and talents from the planet Lu, you are

28:27.580 --> 28:38.740
going to have a world, once again, that is dynamic, that is a synthesis of the
past rather than the repetition of it. And Maxwell has presented science fiction

28:38.740 --> 28:43.260
with two very interesting yet quite different series. She certainly arrived to
watch.

